By Boluwatife Ezekiel Olaleye

Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode, has hailed President Donald Trump’s address at the ongoing United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) in New York.

In a series of tweets on Wednesday evening, Fani-Fayode called Trump “a great man and a strong leader”.

He wrote: “If the righteous many do not confront the wicked few, then evil will triumph”- @realDonaldTrump. A profound and insightful submission.










ALSO SEE: Fani-Kayode blasts Buhari over speech at UN


“Powerful speech by @POTUS @realDonaldTrump at UN yesterday. He inspired the world and gave us hope again. A great man and a strong leader!”

His comments came a day after he criticised President Muhammadu Buhari’s address at the General Assembly.

Fani-Kayode lambasted the president for not condemning killings in Nigeria.





